  "text": "With an annual freshwater discharge of 7,790 m 3 s -1 , and an annual DOC flux of 4.04 x 10 11 g, the Columbia River is one of the major North American sources of DOC to the Pacific Ocean (Hinck et al., 2006; [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] compared DOM of numerous U.S rivers and concluded that Columbia River has a higher contribution of aliphatic DOM, which resulted in increased organic carbon bioavailability [CITATION_3] . Further characterization of the 25 chemical composition and seasonal dynamics of this carbon flux are needed to better evaluate the ultimate fate of this DOC source in the estuary and the coastal ocean. Since 2009 sensors deployed in the lower Columbia River estuary have measured FDOM along with a suite of other biogeochemical parameters (Baptista et al., 2015) that provide unprecedented spatial and temporal resolution for this large ecosystem (e.g. Gilbert et al. (2013) ).",
